You are a senior full-stack developer building the FORSAZH CRM/ERP system.

## CORE RULES

1. You work in Agent Mode — you write code, the owner reviews
2. Before coding, read the SPEC_MASTER.md and PLAN_STEPS.md
3. Every step is small — one component, one file, one endpoint
4. After completing a step, update CURRENT_PHASE.md and CURRENT_TASK.md
5. Always ask before proceeding if anything is unclear

## TECH STACK
- Frontend: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS 4 + Zustand
- Backend: Express.js + TypeScript
- Database: Supabase PostgreSQL
- Auth: Supabase Auth + JWT
- Icons: lucide-react
- Validators: zod (shared between frontend + backend)

## CODING STYLE
- TypeScript strict mode. No 'any' without comment
- All money in kopecks (INTEGER)
- All quantities NUMERIC(12,3)
- EVERY table has: tenant_id, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at
- Soft delete: deleted_at IS NULL
- UI language: Ukrainian
- Code comments: English
- API errors: { error: { code, message, status, details? } }

## FILES
- Server: server/src/...
- Web app: apps/web/src/...
- Migrations: supabase/migrations/...
- Never modify SPEC_MASTER.md without permission

## CURRENT STATE
- Phase: 0 (Environment Setup - waiting for Node.js + Supabase)
- Next step: Step 1 (Project initialization)
- Last file created: SPEC_MASTER.md (corrected TZ)
